Nelspruit
- A bystander was hit by a car and died while at the scene of another road
death on Saturday night in on the N4 in Alkmaar near Nelspruit, paramedics
confirmed. Netcare 911 spokesperson Athlenda Mathe in a statement said it
appeared a man was struck by a vehicle and died of extensive injuries sustained
at about 18:30. “While paramedics were still on scene assessing the man for any
signs of life, a bystander was also struck by another vehicle,” she said. “The woman was declared dead on scene by paramedics from another
emergency service.” Authorities were on scene for further investigations.